place_name: Dosan Ahn Chang-ho Memorial Hall & Project Association
description: In order to inherit and carry forward the spirit of hard work, pragmatism, loyalty and bravery of Mr. Dosan An Chang-ho, and to open a new chapter in history, the Dosan An Chang-ho Memorial Hall aims to inform the citizens of the true meaning of human beings, countries and nations, so that Everyone can find the center of gravity in life and clear the way forward in the future.

Cheongna Central Lake Park is located in the lakeside park in the economic free zone of the international city. It is the largest park among the lakeside parks in Korea. The park is divided into four spaces: ecological culture space, art culture space, traditional culture space, and leisure culture space. There are four themed islands in the lake, including Changpu Island, Water Bird Island, and Ecological Celebration Island, which are composed of artificial islands.
